sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant ServiceCA as OpenShift Service CA<br/>Auto Cert Provisioning
    participant KubeflowCtrl as Kubeflow Notebook Controller<br/>Creates StatefulSets
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS Edge TLS
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,KubeflowCtrl: Flow 1: OAuth Proxy Injection (Notebook Creation)
        User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>annotation: inject-oauth=true<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: AdmissionReview POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>HTTPS/8443, mTLS (API Server Client Cert)
        Webhook->>K8sAPI: Return modified spec<br/>OAuth proxy sidecar injected<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>{notebook-name}<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>{notebook-name}-tls:443→8443<br/>serving-cert annotation<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        ServiceCA->>K8sAPI: Create Secret<br/>{notebook-name}-tls (TLS cert)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret<br/>{notebook-name}-oauth-config<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route (Edge TLS)<br/>External access<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>ctrl-np, oauth-np<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create RoleBinding<br/>elyra-pipelines if DSPA exists<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        KubeflowCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>with injected OAuth sidecar<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Access via OAuth (Runtime)
        User->>Router: HTTPS GET notebook URL<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS1.2+ (Edge), No Auth
        Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward to Service<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS1.2+
        OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: Redirect if no session<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS1.2+
        User->>OAuthServer: Authenticate<br/>HTTPS/443, User Credentials
        OAuthServer->>OAuthProxy: OAuth Token<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS1.2+
        OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Can user GET notebook?<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth Token
        K8sAPI->>OAuthProxy: SAR Result (allowed/denied)<br/>HTTPS/443
        alt Authorized
            OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8888, No Encryption
            Notebook->>OAuthProxy: Response<br/>HTTP/8888
            OAuthProxy->>Router: Response<br/>HTTPS/8443
            Router->>User: Response via Edge TLS<br/>HTTPS/443, Session Cookie
        else Unauthorized
            OAuthProxy->>User: 403 Forbidden
        end
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: Notebook Without OAuth (Direct Access)
        User->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>no OAuth annotation<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route → notebook Service<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>ctrl-np only<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        User->>Router: Access via Route<br/>HTTPS/443, No Auth
        Router->>Notebook: Forward to notebook Service<br/>HTTP/8888
        Notebook->>Router: Response<br/>HTTP/8888
        Router->>User: Response via Edge TLS<br/>HTTPS/443
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 245)
        Note over K8sAPI,Controller: Flow 4: Controller Reconciliation Loop
        K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (Notebook)<br/>create/update/delete<br/>HTTPS/443
        Controller->>K8sAPI: GET Notebook details<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: GET Route (check exists)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Route<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Check OAuth annotation<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        alt inject-oauth=true
            Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update OAuth resources<br/>ServiceAccount, Service, Secrets,<br/>NetworkPolicies, RoleBindings<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
        end
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Notebook status/finalizers<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount Token
    end
